 outside of Mobe Co. The selling price per unit for these sales is $850, with variable costs of $770 per unit. Additionally, Division A engages in external sales by selling adaptors to other companies, while also selling internally to Division B.", "\"SPARE CAPACITY\":\"Spare capacity\" refers to the unused production capacity that can be utilized without incurring additional fixed costs. Division M has spare capacity to produce 28,000 motors. This spare capacity is the unused production capacity of Division M, which is 25,000 units per year after meeting the maximum external demand of 35,000 units.", "\"INCREMENTAL COST\":\"Incremental cost is the additional cost incurred when producing one more unit. For Division S, the incremental cost of buying from outside the group is $60 per unit.\"", "\"GROUP PROFITS\":\"Group profits refer to the total profits of the entire organization, considering both internal and external sales.\"", "\"ETHICAL TRANSFER PRICING SYSTEM\":\"An ethical transfer pricing system ensures decisions are in the best interest of the organization, gives divisional managers autonomy, and allows fair measurement of divisional performance.\"", "\"OPTIMIZING ADAPTOR SUPPLY FOR PORTABLE GARAGE CO (PGC)\":\"The Portable Garage Co (PGC) has two divisions: Division B (battery division) and Division A (adaptor division). Division B uses adaptors from Division A for its upgraded portable batteries, which can charge mobile devices and laptops. Division A also sells adaptors externally. The case involves optimizing the supply and pricing of adaptors between the divisions to maximize group profits.\"", "\"PORTABLE BATTERY\":\"A portable battery is a product sold by Division B that can start a car's engine and charge mobile devices and laptops.\"", "\"ADAPTOR\":\"An adaptor is a product sold by Division A, used to charge mobile devices and laptops by attaching them to a car's internal power source.\"", "\"INTERNAL SALES\":\"Internal sales refer to transactions between divisions within the same company. Division B buys adaptors from Division A.\"", "\"MAXIMUM ANNUAL MARKET DEMAND\":\"Maximum annual market demand is the highest number of units that can be sold in a year. Division B's maximum annual market demand for portable batteries is 180,000 units.\"", "\"CURRENT ANNUAL PRODUCTION CAPACITY\":\"Current annual production capacity is the maximum number of units that can be produced in a year. Division A's current annual production capacity for adaptors is 350,000 units.\"", "\"MAXIMUM ANNUAL EXTERNAL DEMAND\":\"Maximum annual external demand is the highest number of units that can be sold to external customers in a year. Division A's maximum annual external demand for adaptors is not specified.\""], "parameters": {"model": "text-embedding-3-small", "temperature": 0.0, "frequency_penalty": null, "presence_penalty": null, "top_p": 1.0, "max_tokens": 4000, "n": 1}}